NAME
  DIR - List directory contents (Internal)

SYNOPSIS
  DIR [path]
  LS  [path]

DESCRIPTION
  Lists files and subdirectories in
  the specified path. If no path is
  given, lists current directory.

EXAMPLES
  DIR
  DIR /BIN
  LS /USR/SRC

NOTES
  DIR is a built-in shell command.
  It uses a fixed 1KB buffer. For
  very large directories that exceed
  this buffer, use CATALOG.

SEE ALSO
  CATALOG, CD, PWD